AGI - Hamas states that an agreement was reached on the Israeli delay in the release of Palestinian prisoners. The Palestinian Group states that a delegation in Egypt has made some progress towards the implementation of an agreement.
"The delegation of Hamas leadership led by Khalil Al-Hayya concluded his visit to Cairo," where he met Egyptian officials. Discussions were held on the implementation of the ceasefire agreement, the exchange of prisoners and the prospects for the second stage of the negotiations. The delegation of the leadership of the movement underlined its clear position on the need for a full and precise commitment to all its provisions and phases," said the group in a statement. "An agreement was also reached to resolve the issue of the delay in the release of Palestinian prisoners who should have been released in the last batch."
According to the 'Times of Israel', Hamas' agreement with Israel provides for the "simultaneous" release of the bodies of four Israeli hostages and 602 Palestinian prisoners, which would end a stalemate situation that risked the ceasefire agreement to collapse before the completion of its first phase.&nbsp;

