AGI - The President of the United States, Donald Trump, told journalists that the Ukrainian President, Volodymyr Zelensky, will visit the White House on Friday to sign the agreement on minerals>. Two sources close to the Ukrainian government told Axios that the agreement was reached today, after two weeks of negotiations. The agreement - writes Axios - would be designed to allow the United States to draw part of the immense mining wealth of Ukraine and to stimulate the postwar development of the country.
Trump argued that the mineral agreement will generate billions of dollars of revenue for the United States and will help to recover costs related to American support to Ukraine in the war. A source said that Zelensky managed to negotiate a final draft that does not include a key U.S. request, > that it would have had rights on 500 billion dollars of future revenue. The draft agreement states that the United States wants to maintain Ukraine "free, sovereign and secure", but does not refer to specific security guarantees. The White House did not respond immediately to the request for comment.&nbsp;
"I heard Zelensky coming on Friday. Of course, it's okay with me, if you want to sign the agreement with me," Trump responded to the press question in the Oval Studio on the Ukrainian rare land agreement. Trump stressed that the agreement with Ukraine "is very important" and expressed the opinion that the American people "is very happy" for this result. Ukraine has reached an agreement with the United States to allocate 50% of the profits of the exploitation of its natural resources still to be exploited to a common investment fund on which the American part will have greater decision-making power and which will serve to make investments in the Ukrainian economy. According to the publication 'Kyiv Independent', which had the exclusive agreement, the Zelensky government would not have obtained that the Trump administration engaged in writing to continue to militarily support its country

